event: An abrupt period of global warming accelerates the glacial retreat;Jericho has evidence of settlement;
Construction of oldest surviving proto-religious site, in Turkey;

The Indigenous peoples of the southwestern Amazon basin domesticate cassava, the first domestic crop in America, followed by squash and dozens of tree species. They also begin intensively modifying the Amazonian landscape, foresting open savannahs and permanently increasing the biomass and biodiversity of the modern Amazon rainforest;

Domestication of the goat;In northern Mesopotamia, cultivation of barley and wheat begins;Many of the ice age megafauna go extinct;The post-glacial sea level rise decelerates, slowing the submersion of landmasses;
Last mainland species of woolly mammoth die out;
Domestication of the cat;The Sahara desert region supports a savanna-like environment. An African culture develops across the current Sahel region.;
First human settlement in Amman, Jordan;

Early European Farmers arrive in Europe through Anatolia.;Human settlement of Mehrgarh, one of the earliest sites with evidence of farming and herding in South Asia;Jiahu culture begins in China.;Maize is domesticated in southern Mexico;The Kuk Swamp in the highlands of Papua New Guinea becomes a cradle of agriculture. Early farmers dig canals that transform the swamp into arable land
Sudden decrease of global temperatures, probably caused by the final collapse of the Laurentide Ice Sheet;Sudden rise in sea level by 6.5 m in less than 140 years;
Development of proto-writing in China, Southeast Europe, and West Asia;The earliest American ceramics are created in the Amazon basin;
Copper smelting in evidence in Pločnik and Belovode;
Akahoya eruption creates the Kikai Caldera and ends the earliest homogeneous Jomon culture in Japan;
Toggling harpoons are invented somewhere in eastern Siberia, spreading south into Japan and east into North America;
Civilizations develop in the Mesopotamia/Fertile Crescent region;Domestication of the horse and the chicken;
The first monumental buildings are constructed in Sechin Bajo, now Peru.;
End of the African humid period;First evidence of mummification in Egypt;Invention of the wheel;Rise of the Sumerian Civilization (Mesopotamia);
Bronze Age begins (widespread use of bronze tools and weapons);

Sumerian cuneiform writing system is first used, triggering the beginning of recorded history;The Norte Chico civilization begins on the coast of Peru construction and founding of the first cities in the Americas;
Early dynastic period in Egypt begins;
The construction of the Pyramids in Egypt begins;
Establishment of the Code of Ur-Nammu (oldest known law code);
Large-scale irrigation systems (e.g., Nile, Tigris-Euphrates);Minoan civilization flourishes on Crete;Rise of major civilizations (Mesopotamia, Egypt, Indus Valley, China);
First Babylonian Empire established under Hammurabi;
Fall of the Western Roman Empire;
Columbian Exchange and ecological disruption (species invasion);
Industrial Revolution begins in Britain;Large-scale coal burning for energy;Urbanization and factory systems;
Discovery of CO2's greenhouse effect by Svante Arrhenius;
Widespread use of fossil fuel-powered automobiles;
First man on the moon;Internet invented;
Montreal Protocol to phase out CFCs;
Anthropocene rejected as a new geological epoch;
